overview: The user initiated a request for a complete aesthetic overhaul of
  their sleep questionnaire application, feeling its current design was too
  generic. The assistant undertook a detailed review of the app's visual
  elements, including color palette, typography, spacing, form elements, and
  overall visual interest. Based on this analysis, a new design strategy was
  formulated to introduce a calming, sleep-themed aesthetic. This involved
  updating the global CSS with a new color palette, enhancing the main
  questionnaire form layout, improving the progress bar, redesigning the intro
  section with feature cards and refined alerts, and polishing individual UI
  components like checkboxes, sliders, and radio buttons. The report section was
  also updated to align with the new, more professional and engaging visual
  language.
